about 35 minutes ago

309
00:24:42,369 --> 00:24:44,038
General Jack Ripper,

310
00:24:44,121 --> 00:24:47,917
the commanding general
of Burpelson Air Force Base,

311
00:24:48,918 --> 00:24:52,213
issued an order
to the 34 B-52's of his wing,

312
00:24:52,296 --> 00:24:54,507
which were airborne at the time

313
00:24:54,590 --> 00:24:58,677
as part of a special exercise
we were holding called Operation Dropkick.

314
00:24:58,761 --> 00:25:04,391
Now, it appears that the order
called for the planes to

315
00:25:04,475 --> 00:25:06,852
attack their targets inside Russia.

316
00:25:08,479 --> 00:25:11,190
The planes are fully armed
with nuclear weapons

317
00:25:11,273 --> 00:25:14,735
with an average load
of 40 megatons each.

318
00:25:14,818 --> 00:25:19,281
Now, the central display of Russia
will indicate the position of the planes.

319
00:25:20,658 --> 00:25:23,911
The triangles are their primary targets.

320
00:25:23,994 --> 00:25:27,957
The squares are their secondary targets.

321
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:33,170
The aircraft will begin penetrating
Russian radar cover within 25 minutes.

322
00:25:35,464 --> 00:25:38,801
General Turgidson, I find this
very difficult to understand.

323
00:25:38,884 --> 00:25:41,637
I was under the impression
that I was the only one in authority

324
00:25:41,720 --> 00:25:44,265
to order the use of nuclear weapons.

325
00:25:45,349 --> 00:25:46,892
That's right, sir.

326
00:25:46,976 --> 00:25:49,395
You are the only person
authorized to do so.

327
00:25:49,478 --> 00:25:53,691
And although I hate to judge
before all the facts are in,

328
00:25:53,774 --> 00:25:57,570
it's beginning to look like General Ripper
exceeded his authority.

329
00:25:57,653 --> 00:26:01,699
It certainly does, far beyond the point
I would have imagined possible.

330
00:26:02,616 --> 00:26:06,161
Well, perhaps you're forgetting
the provisions of plan "R", sir.

331
00:26:06,745 --> 00:26:08,122
Plan "R"?

332
00:26:09,456 --> 00:26:12,918
Plan "R" is an emergency war plan

333
00:26:13,002 --> 00:26:15,045
in which a lower-echelon commander

334
00:26:15,129 --> 00:26:18,841
may order nuclear retaliation
after a sneak attack

335
00:26:18,924 --> 00:26:22,261
if the normal chain of command
has been disrupted.

336
00:26:22,344 --> 00:26:25,431
You approved it, sir.
You must remember.

337
00:26:26,473 --> 00:26:30,769
Surely you must recall, sir, when
Senator Buford made that big hassle

338
00:26:30,853 --> 00:26:33,731
about our deterrent lacking credibility.

339
00:26:33,814 --> 00:26:38,652
The idea was for plan "R" to be
a sort of retaliatory safeguard.

340
00:26:38,736 --> 00:26:40,613
A safeguard?

341
00:26:40,696 --> 00:26:43,949
Well, I admit the human element
seems to have failed us here.

342
00:26:44,033 --> 00:26:47,328
But the idea was to discourage
the Russkies from any hope

343
00:26:47,411 --> 00:26:50,039
that they could knock out Washington,
and yourself, sir,

344
00:26:50,122 --> 00:26:52,124
as part of a general sneak attack

345
00:26:52,207 --> 00:26:56,295
and escape retaliation because of
lack of proper command and control.

346
00:26:56,378 --> 00:26:59,173
Well, I assume then that the planes
will return automatically

347
00:26:59,256 --> 00:27:01,300
once they reach their fail-safe points.

348
00:27:01,383 --> 00:27:03,135
Well, no, sir, I'm afraid not.

349
00:27:03,218 --> 00:27:06,847
You see, the planes were holding
at their fail-safe points,

350
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:08,932
when the go code was issued.

351
00:27:09,016 --> 00:27:10,976
Now, once they fly beyond fail-safe,

352
00:27:11,060 --> 00:27:13,604
they do not require
a second order to proceed.

353
00:27:13,687 --> 00:27:15,648
They will continue
until they reach their targets.

354
00:27:15,731 --> 00:27:18,734
Then why haven't you radioed the planes
countermanding the go code?

355
00:27:20,069 --> 00:27:23,447
Well, I'm afraid we're unable to
communicate with any of the aircraft.

356
00:27:23,530 --> 00:27:25,240
Why?

357
00:27:25,324 --> 00:27:28,035
As you may recall, sir,

358
00:27:28,118 --> 00:27:31,830
one of the provisions
of plan "R" provides

359
00:27:31,914 --> 00:27:36,543
that once the go code is received

360
00:27:36,627 --> 00:27:40,214
the normal SSB radios in the aircraft

361
00:27:40,297 --> 00:27:42,341
are switched into
a special coded device

362
00:27:42,424 --> 00:27:45,552
which, I believe,
is designated as CRM 114.

363
00:27:45,636 --> 00:27:49,932
Now, in order to prevent the enemy
from issuing fake or confusing orders,

364
00:27:50,015 --> 00:27:54,061
CRM 114 is designed
not to receive at all

365
00:27:54,144 --> 00:27:59,149
unless the message is preceded by
the correct three-letter code group prefix.

366
00:28:00,317 --> 00:28:02,319
Then do you mean to tell me,
General Turgidson,

367
00:28:02,403 --> 00:28:05,114
that you will be unable
to recall the aircraft?

368
00:28:05,197 --> 00:28:06,740
That's about the size of it, sir.

369
00:28:06,824 --> 00:28:11,203
However, we are plowing through every
possible three-letter combination of the code.

370
00:28:11,286 --> 00:28:16,250
But since there are,
17,000 permutations,

371
00:28:16,333 --> 00:28:20,087
it's going to take us about
two and a half days to transmit them all.

372
00:28:20,170 --> 00:28:22,923
How soon did you say the planes
would penetrate Russian radar cover?

373
00:28:23,006 --> 00:28:24,925
About 18 minutes from now, sir.

374
00:28:25,008 --> 00:28:27,845
- Are you in contact with General Ripper?
- No, sir, no.

375
00:28:27,928 --> 00:28:31,473
General Ripper sealed off the base
and cut off all communications.

376
00:28:31,557 --> 00:28:33,225
Where did you get all this information?

377
00:28:33,308 --> 00:28:36,770
General Ripper called
Strategic Air Command headquarters

378
00:28:36,854 --> 00:28:39,106
shortly after he issued the go code.

379
00:28:39,189 --> 00:28:43,026
I have a portion of the transcript of that
conversation, if you'd like me to read it.

380
00:28:43,110 --> 00:28:44,403
Read it.

381
00:28:46,697 --> 00:28:50,159
The duty officer asked General Ripper
to confirm the fact

382
00:28:50,242 --> 00:28:53,787
that he had issued
the go code and he said...

383
00:28:53,871 --> 00:28:58,250
Yes, gentlemen, they are on their way
and no one can bring them back.

384
00:28:58,751 --> 00:29:01,044
For the sake of our country
and our way of life,

385
00:29:01,128 --> 00:29:03,839
I suggest you get the rest of SAC
in after them.

386
00:29:03,922 --> 00:29:08,177
Otherwise we will be totally
destroyed by Red retaliation.

387
00:29:08,844 --> 00:29:11,597
My boys will give you
the best kind of start,

388
00:29:11,680 --> 00:29:14,224
1,400 megatons worth,

389
00:29:14,308 --> 00:29:17,811
and you sure as hell
won't stop them now.

390
00:29:17,895 --> 00:29:20,689
So let's get going.
There's no other choice.

391
00:29:20,773 --> 00:29:23,609
God willing, we will prevail,

392
00:29:23,692 --> 00:29:25,694
in peace and freedom from fear,

393
00:29:26,195 --> 00:29:29,114
and in true health
through the purity

394
00:29:29,198 --> 00:29:31,617
and essence of our natural...

395
00:29:33,118 --> 00:29:34,620
fluids.

396
00:29:35,537 --> 00:29:37,206
God bless you all.

397
00:29:39,374 --> 00:29:41,168
Then he hung up.

398
00:29:42,252 --> 00:29:45,714
We're still trying to figure out
the meaning of that last phrase, sir.

399
00:29:45,798 --> 00:29:48,217
There's nothing to figure out,
General Turgidson.

400
00:29:48,300 --> 00:29:50,302
This man is obviously a psychotic.

401
00:29:50,886 --> 00:29:53,514
Well, I'd like to hold off judgment
on a thing like that, sir,

402
00:29:53,597 --> 00:29:55,474
until all the facts are in.

403
00:29:55,557 --> 00:29:59,978
General Turgidson, when you instituted
the human reliability tests,

404
00:30:00,062 --> 00:30:04,149
you assured me there was no possibility
of such a thing ever occurring.

405
00:30:06,026 --> 00:30:09,988
Well, I don't think it's quite fair
to condemn a whole program

406
00:30:10,072 --> 00:30:11,949
because of a single slip-up, sir.

407
00:30:12,950 --> 00:30:15,494
I want to speak to General Ripper
on the telephone personally.

408
00:30:15,577 --> 00:30:17,079
I'm afraid that's impossible, sir.

409
00:30:17,162 --> 00:30:20,958
General Turgidson, I am becoming
less and less interested

410
00:30:21,041 --> 00:30:24,253
in your estimates
of what is possible and impossible.

411
00:30:25,921 --> 00:30:28,423
- General Faceman.
- Yes, sir.

412
00:30:28,507 --> 00:30:31,009
Are there any army units
stationed anywhere near Burpelson?

413
00:30:31,093 --> 00:30:33,262
I'll just check, sir.

414
00:30:37,641 --> 00:30:39,142
Hello.

415
00:30:40,894 --> 00:30:44,523
