788
00:55:32,468 --> 00:55:34,303
We're okay here.

789
00:55:36,305 --> 00:55:38,015
Mandrake.

790
00:55:38,098 --> 00:55:40,351
Do you realize that in addition
to fluoridating water, why,

791
00:55:40,434 --> 00:55:45,230
there are studies under way
to fluoridate salt, flour, fruit juices,

792
00:55:45,314 --> 00:55:49,151
soup, sugar, milk, ice cream?

793
00:55:49,234 --> 00:55:51,779
Ice cream, Mandrake.
Children's ice cream.

794
00:55:51,862 --> 00:55:53,030
Good Lord.

795
00:55:53,113 --> 00:55:55,157
Do you know
when fluoridation first began?

796
00:55:56,617 --> 00:55:58,452
No, no, I don't, Jack.

797
00:55:58,535 --> 00:56:00,954
1946.

798
00:56:01,038 --> 00:56:04,124
1946, Mandrake.

799
00:56:04,208 --> 00:56:07,252
How does that coincide with
your postwar commie conspiracy, huh?

800
00:56:08,295 --> 00:56:11,298
It's incredibly obvious, isn't it?

801
00:56:11,382 --> 00:56:17,096
A foreign substance is introduced
into our precious bodily fluids

802
00:56:17,179 --> 00:56:20,432
without the knowledge of the individual

803
00:56:20,516 --> 00:56:22,851
and certainly without any choice.

804
00:56:24,186 --> 00:56:26,772
That's the way
your hard-core commie works.

805
00:56:28,857 --> 00:56:31,443
Jack, Jack, listen. Tell me.

806
00:56:31,527 --> 00:56:34,947
Tell me, Jack, when did you
first become...

807
00:56:35,030 --> 00:56:37,908
well, develop this theory?

808
00:56:38,992 --> 00:56:41,036
Well, I...

809
00:56:41,120 --> 00:56:44,748
I first became aware of it, Mandrake,

810
00:56:44,832 --> 00:56:47,084
during the physical act of love.

811
00:56:48,752 --> 00:56:54,675
Yes, a profound sense of fatigue,
a feeling of emptiness followed.

812
00:56:55,676 --> 00:56:59,346
Luckily, I was able to interpret
these feelings correctly.

813
00:57:00,848 --> 00:57:02,474
Loss of essence.

814
00:57:02,558 --> 00:57:04,017
Yeah.

815
00:57:04,101 --> 00:57:07,020
I can assure you
it has not recurred, Mandrake.

816
00:57:07,980 --> 00:57:11,733
Women sense my power

817
00:57:11,817 --> 00:57:13,944
and they seek the life essence.

818
00:57:15,404 --> 00:57:18,824
- I do not avoid women, Mandrake.
- No.

819
00:57:18,907 --> 00:57:21,785
But I do deny them my essence.

820
00:57:21,869 --> 00:57:24,705
Yes, Jack.

821
00:57:37,384 --> 00:57:39,761
Cease fire!

822
00:58:00,616 --> 00:58:02,618
The boys must have surrendered.

823
00:58:02,701 --> 00:58:04,912
Well, there it is.

824
00:58:04,995 --> 00:58:06,747
Now, Jack, listen,

825
00:58:06,830 --> 00:58:10,000
while there's still time, I beg you,
let's recall the wing and...

826
00:58:12,211 --> 00:58:14,630
Those boys were like my children,
Mandrake.

827
00:58:16,632 --> 00:58:18,217
Now they've let me down.

828
00:58:18,300 --> 00:58:20,135
No, no, Jack, not a bit of it.

829
00:58:20,219 --> 00:58:23,347
No, I'm sure they all gave
of their very best.

830
00:58:23,430 --> 00:58:25,933
And I'm equally sure they all died
thinking of you...

831
00:58:26,016 --> 00:58:28,852
every man Jack of them... Jack.

832
00:58:28,936 --> 00:58:31,313
Supposing a bit of water has gone off?

833
00:58:31,396 --> 00:58:34,107
Certainly one can never be too sure
about those sort of things.

834
00:58:34,191 --> 00:58:37,069
But you look at me now.
Do I look all rancid and clotted?

835
00:58:37,152 --> 00:58:39,613
You look at me, Jack, eh?
Look, eh?

836
00:58:39,696 --> 00:58:43,283
I drink a lot of water, you know.
I'm what you might call a water man, Jack.

837
00:58:43,367 --> 00:58:44,368
That's what I am.

838
00:58:44,451 --> 00:58:47,371
And I can swear to you, my boy,
swear to you,

839
00:58:47,454 --> 00:58:49,706
that there's nothing wrong
with my bodily fluids.

840
00:58:49,790 --> 00:58:52,334
Not a thing, Jackie.

841
00:58:52,417 --> 00:58:54,711
Mandrake, were you ever
a prisoner of war?

842
00:58:54,795 --> 00:58:58,382
Well, Jack, the time's running very...

843
00:58:58,465 --> 00:59:01,260
- What?
- Were you ever a prisoner of war?

844
00:59:01,343 --> 00:59:03,971
Yes, I was,
as a matter of fact, Jack, I was.

845
00:59:04,054 --> 00:59:07,432
- Did they torture you?
- Yes, they did.

846
00:59:07,516 --> 00:59:10,227
I was tortured by the Japanese,
Jack, if you must know.

847
00:59:10,310 --> 00:59:12,896
- Not a pretty story.
- Well, what happened?

848
00:59:12,980 --> 00:59:15,065
Oh, well, I don't know, Jack.

849
00:59:15,148 --> 00:59:17,693
It's difficult to think of
under these conditions,

850
00:59:17,776 --> 00:59:20,904
but, well, what happened
was they got me on the old

851
00:59:20,988 --> 00:59:23,448
Rangoon-Ichinawa Railway.

852
00:59:23,532 --> 00:59:27,869
I was laying train lines
for the bloody Japanese puff-puffs.

853
00:59:27,953 --> 00:59:31,206
No, I mean,
when they tortured you, did you talk?

854
00:59:33,041 --> 00:59:36,837
No, I... Well, I don't think
they wanted me to talk, really.

855
00:59:36,920 --> 00:59:39,298
I don't think they wanted me
to say anything.

856
00:59:39,381 --> 00:59:42,426
It was just their way of having
a bit of fun, the swines.

857
00:59:42,509 --> 00:59:46,013
The strange thing is
they make such bloody good cameras.

858
00:59:47,681 --> 00:59:50,934
You know, those clowns outside are
gonna give me a pretty good going over

859
00:59:51,018 --> 00:59:53,520
in a few minutes, for the code.

860
00:59:53,604 --> 00:59:55,105
Yes...

861
00:59:56,440 --> 00:59:59,943
Yes, well, you may have...
You may have quite a point there, Jack.

862
01:00:01,028 --> 01:00:03,739
I don't know how well
I could stand up under torture.

863
01:00:03,822 --> 01:00:07,242
Well, of course, the answer to that
is, boy, no one ever does.

864
01:00:07,326 --> 01:00:11,455
And my advice to you, Jack,
is to give me the code now,

865
01:00:11,538 --> 01:00:14,333
and if those devils come back
and try any rough stuff,

866
01:00:14,416 --> 01:00:17,836
we'll fight 'em together, boy,
like we did just now on the floor, eh?

867
01:00:17,919 --> 01:00:21,465
You with your gun, and me with the belt
and the ammo, feeding you, Jack.

868
01:00:21,548 --> 01:00:24,301
"Feed me", you said,
and I was feeding you, Jack.

869
01:00:24,384 --> 01:00:26,970
You know, Mandrake,

870
01:00:27,054 --> 01:00:30,057
I happen to believe
in a life after this one,

871
01:00:31,808 --> 01:00:34,519
and I know I'll have to answer
for what I've done.

872
01:00:37,022 --> 01:00:38,482
And I think I can.

873
01:00:38,565 --> 01:00:41,902
Yes, well, of course you can, Jack.
Of course you can. You can.

874
01:00:41,985 --> 01:00:44,154
I'm a religious man myself,
you know, Jack.

875
01:00:44,237 --> 01:00:47,824
I believe in all that sort of thing,
and I'm hoping you know, Jack.

