Don't you know that General Ripper
went as mad as a bloody March hare

965
01:07:16,546 --> 01:07:19,841
and sent the whole wing
to attack the Soviets?

966
01:07:19,924 --> 01:07:23,386
- What are you talking about?
- I'll tell you what I'm talking about.

967
01:07:23,470 --> 01:07:27,515
I'm going to pick up this red telephone,
which is connected to SAC,

968
01:07:27,599 --> 01:07:30,351
and I hope...

969
01:07:30,435 --> 01:07:32,771
Blast. Blast.

970
01:07:32,854 --> 01:07:36,858
Shot away, I expect, by one of your men
during this ridiculous fighting.

971
01:07:38,193 --> 01:07:40,403
Right.

972
01:07:40,487 --> 01:07:43,782
All right, Charlie, I've been
wasting too much time on you.

973
01:07:43,865 --> 01:07:46,117
I've got a lot of wounded men outside.

974
01:07:46,201 --> 01:07:47,744
Start walking.

975
01:08:09,849 --> 01:08:13,853
All the radio gear is out,
including the CRM 114.

976
01:08:13,937 --> 01:08:17,107
I think the auto-destruct mechanism
got hit and blew itself up.

977
01:08:21,569 --> 01:08:24,781
The fire is out.
Emergency power is on.

978
01:08:24,864 --> 01:08:28,368
Everything seems to check out all right.
Will advise.

979
01:08:28,451 --> 01:08:30,161
Roger. Navigator.

980
01:08:30,245 --> 01:08:35,625
I've worked out our rate of fuel loss
at approximately 162 per minute.

981
01:08:35,708 --> 01:08:38,503
This gives us a radius of action
sufficient to take out

982
01:08:38,586 --> 01:08:40,797
primary and secondary targets,

983
01:08:40,880 --> 01:08:44,509
but we will not - repeat -
not be able to make it back

984
01:08:44,592 --> 01:08:46,302
to any base or neutral country.

985
01:08:47,262 --> 01:08:52,100
However, we would have enough fuel
to ditch at weather ship Tango Delta,

986
01:08:52,183 --> 01:08:55,895
grid coordinates 003691.

987
01:09:00,733 --> 01:09:02,986
Well, boys, we got three engines out,

988
01:09:03,069 --> 01:09:06,865
we got more holes in us
than a horse trader's mule,

989
01:09:06,948 --> 01:09:09,159
the radio is gone
and we're leaking fuel,

990
01:09:09,242 --> 01:09:12,579
and if we was flying any lower,
why, we'd need sleigh bells on this thing.

991
01:09:12,662 --> 01:09:15,623
But we got one little budge
on them Russkies.

992
01:09:15,707 --> 01:09:17,667
At this height,
why, they might harpoon us,

993
01:09:17,750 --> 01:09:20,879
but they dang sure ain't gonna
spot us on no radar screen.

994
01:09:32,015 --> 01:09:33,892
The other way.

995
01:09:33,975 --> 01:09:36,853
- Where are you taking me?
- The main gate.

996
01:09:36,936 --> 01:09:38,479
Colonel!

997
01:09:38,563 --> 01:09:42,025
Colonel, I must know what you think
has been going on here.

998
01:09:42,108 --> 01:09:43,902
- You want to know what I think?
- Yes.

999
01:09:43,985 --> 01:09:46,779
I think you're some kind
of deviated "prevert".

1000
01:09:46,863 --> 01:09:49,365
And I think General Ripper
found out about your "preversion",

1001
01:09:49,449 --> 01:09:52,118
and that you were organizing
some kind of mutiny of "preverts".

1002
01:09:52,202 --> 01:09:54,204
Now move.

1003
01:09:54,287 --> 01:09:57,415
On top of that, I don't know anything
about any planes attacking Russia.

1004
01:09:57,498 --> 01:10:01,586
I was told to get General Ripper on the phone
with the president of the United States.

1005
01:10:01,669 --> 01:10:06,549
Now, just one second.
You just said "the president".

1006
01:10:06,633 --> 01:10:08,718
What about the president?

1007
01:10:08,801 --> 01:10:11,971
Now, the president wants to speak
to General Ripper, doesn't he?

1008
01:10:12,055 --> 01:10:14,641
Now, General Ripper is dead,
is he not?

1009
01:10:14,724 --> 01:10:16,851
I am General Ripper's executive officer,

1010
01:10:16,935 --> 01:10:20,063
so the president will bloody well
want to speak to me, won't he?

1011
01:10:20,146 --> 01:10:23,733
There's a telephone box over there
and the line may be open.

1012
01:10:23,816 --> 01:10:26,527
You want to talk to the president
of the United States?

1013
01:10:26,611 --> 01:10:29,489
I don't want to talk to him, Colonel.
I've got to talk to him.

1014
01:10:29,572 --> 01:10:33,409
And I can assure you, if you don't put that
gun away and stop this stupid nonsense,

1015
01:10:33,493 --> 01:10:37,747
the Court of Inquiry on this'll
give you such a pranging,

1016
01:10:37,830 --> 01:10:41,626
you'll be lucky if you end up wearing
the uniform of a bloody toilet attendant!

1017
01:10:45,505 --> 01:10:47,340
Okay. Go ahead.

1018
01:10:47,423 --> 01:10:50,718
Try and get the president
of the United States on the phone.

1019
01:10:52,929 --> 01:10:56,182
If you try any "preversions" in there,
I'll blow your head off.

1020
01:11:09,529 --> 01:11:12,240
Operator?
This is Group Captain Lionel Mandrake.

1021
01:11:12,323 --> 01:11:14,450
I'm speaking
from Burpelson Air Force Base.

1022
01:11:14,534 --> 01:11:16,202
Look, something very urgent has come up

1023
01:11:16,286 --> 01:11:18,371
and I want you to place
an emergency person-to-person call

1024
01:11:18,454 --> 01:11:21,541
with President Merkin Muffley
in the Pentagon, Washington, DC.

1025
01:11:22,834 --> 01:11:26,170
Burpelson 39180.

1026
01:11:27,547 --> 01:11:29,716
No. I'm perfectly serious, Operator.
The president.

1027
01:11:29,799 --> 01:11:32,302
Yes, the president
of the United States.

1028
01:11:32,385 --> 01:11:34,512
Oh. I'm sorry.
I haven't got enough change.

1029
01:11:34,595 --> 01:11:36,472
Could you...

1030
01:11:36,556 --> 01:11:38,891
Could you make this
a collect call, Operator?

1031
01:11:51,154 --> 01:11:53,406
Just one second, Operator.

1032
01:11:53,489 --> 01:11:55,992
They won't accept the call.
Have you got 55 cents?

1033
01:11:56,075 --> 01:11:59,537
Well, you don't think I'd go into combat
with loose change in my pocket, do you?

1034
01:12:01,873 --> 01:12:03,374
Operator?

1035
01:12:03,458 --> 01:12:05,001
Look...

1036
01:12:05,084 --> 01:12:08,254
is it possible to make this
an ordinary trunk call?

1037
01:12:08,338 --> 01:12:13,676
Well, what do you call it?
You know... Oh, station to station.

1038
01:12:18,348 --> 01:12:21,351
Oh, blast! I'm still 20 cents short.

1039
01:12:23,644 --> 01:12:27,023
Operator, hold on.
I shan't keep you a second.

1040
01:12:27,106 --> 01:12:29,692
Colonel, that Coca-Cola machine.

1041
01:12:29,776 --> 01:12:33,613
I want you to shoot the lock off it.
There may be some change in there.

1042
01:12:37,033 --> 01:12:38,534
That's private property.

1043
01:12:38,618 --> 01:12:41,537
Colonel, can you possibly imagine
what is going to happen to you,

1044
01:12:41,621 --> 01:12:44,248
your frame, outlook,
way of life and everything,

1045
01:12:44,332 --> 01:12:47,085
when they've learned that you
have obstructed a telephone call

1046
01:12:47,168 --> 01:12:48,920
to the president of the United States?

1047
01:12:49,003 --> 01:12:51,172
Can you imagine?

1048
01:12:51,255 --> 01:12:53,925
Shoot it off! Shoot with a gun.

1049
01:12:54,008 --> 01:12:56,677
That's what the bullets are for, you twit!

1050
01:12:56,761 --> 01:12:58,262
Okay.

1051
01:12:58,346 --> 01:13:00,056
I'm gonna get your money for you.

1052
01:13:00,139 --> 01:13:03,059
But if you don't get the president
of the United States on that phone,

1053
01:13:03,142 --> 01:13:04,977
- you know what's going to happen to you?
- What?

1054
01:13:05,061 --> 01:13:08,314
You're gonna have to answer
to the Coca-Cola company.

