1064
01:13:48,688 --> 01:13:51,482
Gentlemen, gentlemen.

1065
01:13:51,566 --> 01:13:53,901
Gentlemen.

1066
01:13:53,985 --> 01:13:55,945
Mr. President.

1067
01:13:56,028 --> 01:13:58,281
I'm not a sentimentalist
at all by nature,

1068
01:13:58,364 --> 01:14:01,492
but I think I know
what's in every heart in this room.

1069
01:14:01,576 --> 01:14:04,704
I think we ought to
all just bow our heads

1070
01:14:04,787 --> 01:14:07,415
and give a short prayer of thanks
for our deliverance.

1071
01:14:07,498 --> 01:14:10,209
Lord!

1072
01:14:10,293 --> 01:14:14,839
We have heard the wings
of the angel of death

1073
01:14:14,922 --> 01:14:17,675
fluttering over our heads
from the valley of fear.

1074
01:14:17,758 --> 01:14:20,553
You have seen fit to deliver us
from the forces of evil.

1075
01:14:20,636 --> 01:14:22,305
Excuse me, sir.

1076
01:14:22,388 --> 01:14:25,475
Premier Kissoff's calling again,
and he's hopping mad.

1077
01:14:32,231 --> 01:14:36,027
