Roger. Three miles.

1238
01:26:42,628 --> 01:26:44,296
Target in sight!

1239
01:26:44,379 --> 01:26:46,381
Where in hell is Major Kong?

1240
01:27:10,155 --> 01:27:11,406
Hey, what about Major Kong?

1241
01:27:39,768 --> 01:27:41,270
Mr. President.

1242
01:27:41,353 --> 01:27:46,441
I would not rule out the chance to preserve
a nucleus of human specimens.

1243
01:27:46,525 --> 01:27:49,444
It would be quite easy.

1244
01:27:51,780 --> 01:27:56,952
At the bottom of some
of our deeper mine shafts.

1245
01:27:57,035 --> 01:28:01,623
The radioactivity would never penetrate
a mine some thousands of feet deep.

1246
01:28:01,707 --> 01:28:06,169
And in a matter of weeks,
sufficient improvements in dwelling space

1247
01:28:06,253 --> 01:28:08,297
could easily be provided.

1248
01:28:08,380 --> 01:28:10,757
How long would you have to
stay down there?

1249
01:28:10,841 --> 01:28:12,801
Well, let's see now...

1250
01:28:14,928 --> 01:28:16,930
Cobalt Thorium G.

1251
01:28:27,858 --> 01:28:30,819
Radioactive half-life of...

1252
01:28:33,864 --> 01:28:37,326
I would think that possibly...

1253
01:28:37,409 --> 01:28:38,910
100 years.

1254
01:28:40,829 --> 01:28:44,875
You mean, people could actually
stay down there for a hundred years?

1255
01:28:44,958 --> 01:28:47,002
It would not be difficult, <i>mein Führer</i>.

1256
01:28:47,085 --> 01:28:49,004
Nuclear reactors could...

1257
01:28:49,087 --> 01:28:51,840
I'm sorry, Mr. President.

1258
01:28:51,923 --> 01:28:55,761
Nuclear reactors could provide power
almost indefinitely.

1259
01:28:55,844 --> 01:28:58,597
Greenhouses could maintain plant life.

1260
01:28:58,680 --> 01:29:01,600
Animals could be bred and slaughtered

1261
01:29:02,434 --> 01:29:06,897
A quick survey would have to be made
of all the available mine sites in the country,

1262
01:29:06,980 --> 01:29:09,941
but I would guess that...

1263
01:29:10,025 --> 01:29:14,529
dwelling space for several hundred thousands
of our people could easily be provided.

1264
01:29:14,613 --> 01:29:20,535
Well, I would hate to have to decide
who stays up and who goes down.

1265
01:29:20,619 --> 01:29:23,413
Well, that would not
be necessary, Mr. President.

1266
01:29:24,664 --> 01:29:27,542
It could easily be accomplished
with a computer,

1267
01:29:27,626 --> 01:29:29,920
and the computer could be set
and programmed

1268
01:29:30,003 --> 01:29:35,967
to accept factors from youth, health,
sexual fertility, intelligence,

1269
01:29:36,051 --> 01:29:38,887
and a cross section
of necessary skills.

1270
01:29:38,970 --> 01:29:41,223
Of course, it would be absolutely vital

1271
01:29:41,306 --> 01:29:45,185
that our top government
and military men be included

1272
01:29:45,268 --> 01:29:47,813
to foster and impart
the required principles

1273
01:29:47,896 --> 01:29:50,148
of leadership and tradition.

1274
01:29:56,154 --> 01:29:59,074
Naturally, they would breed
prodigiously?

1275
01:29:59,157 --> 01:30:01,993
There would be much time
and little to do.

1276
01:30:03,620 --> 01:30:05,747
But with the proper breeding techniques

1277
01:30:05,831 --> 01:30:11,211
and a ratio of, say,
10 females to each male,

1278
01:30:11,294 --> 01:30:13,713
I would guess that they
could then work their way back

1279
01:30:13,797 --> 01:30:17,968
to the present gross national product
within, say, 20 years.

1280
01:30:19,010 --> 01:30:22,347
But look here, Doctor,
wouldn't this nucleus of survivors

1281
01:30:22,431 --> 01:30:25,851
be so grief stricken and anguished
that they'd...

1282
01:30:26,893 --> 01:30:30,605
well, envy the dead
and not want to go on living?

1283
01:30:30,689 --> 01:30:33,442
And also... Excuse me.

1284
01:30:42,701 --> 01:30:46,788
Also, when they go down into the mine,
everyone would still be alive.

1285
01:30:46,872 --> 01:30:48,874
There will be no shocking memories,

1286
01:30:48,957 --> 01:30:53,628
and the prevailing emotion will be
one of nostalgia for those left behind,

1287
01:30:53,712 --> 01:30:59,009
combined with a spirit of bold curiosity
for the adventure ahead.

1288
01:31:16,610 --> 01:31:18,111
Doctor,

1289
01:31:20,739 --> 01:31:23,158
you mentioned the ratio

1290
01:31:23,241 --> 01:31:26,119
of 10 women to each man.

1291
01:31:26,203 --> 01:31:29,247
Now, wouldn't that necessitate
the abandonment

1292
01:31:29,331 --> 01:31:33,126
of the so-called monogamous
sexual relationship?

1293
01:31:33,210 --> 01:31:36,421
I mean, as far
as men were concerned?

1294
01:31:36,505 --> 01:31:38,340
Regrettably, yes.

1295
01:31:38,423 --> 01:31:43,678
But it is, you know, a sacrifice required
for the future of the human race.

1296
01:31:43,762 --> 01:31:48,892
I hasten to add that since each man
will be required to do prodigious...

1297
01:31:50,644 --> 01:31:52,395
service along these lines,

1298
01:31:52,479 --> 01:31:56,399
the women will have to be selected
for their sexual... characteristics,

1299
01:31:56,483 --> 01:32:00,278
which will have to be
of a highly stimulating nature.

1300
01:32:00,362 --> 01:32:04,241
I must confess, you have
an astonishingly good idea there, Doctor.

1301
01:32:05,617 --> 01:32:06,785
Thank you, sir.

1302
01:32:07,536 --> 01:32:11,331
I think we ought to look at this from
the military point of view. I mean...

1303
01:32:12,541 --> 01:32:16,962
supposing the Russkies stashed away
some big bombs, see, and we didn't.

1304
01:32:17,045 --> 01:32:19,923
When they come out in a hundred years,
they could take over.

1305
01:32:20,006 --> 01:32:21,550
I agree, Mr. President.

1306
01:32:21,633 --> 01:32:25,178
They might try an immediate sneak attack
so they could take over our mine shaft space.

1307
01:32:25,262 --> 01:32:28,056
Yeah. I think it would be
extremely naive of us, Mr. President,

1308
01:32:28,139 --> 01:32:31,017
to imagine that these new developments
are going to cause any change

1309
01:32:31,101 --> 01:32:33,061
in Soviet expansionist policy.

1310
01:32:33,144 --> 01:32:35,939
I mean, we must be
increasingly on the alert

1311
01:32:36,022 --> 01:32:38,567
to prevent them from taking over
other mine shaft space

1312
01:32:38,650 --> 01:32:40,735
in order to breed more prodigiously
than we do,

1313
01:32:40,819 --> 01:32:43,738
thus knocking us out through
superior numbers when we emerge.

1314
01:32:43,822 --> 01:32:47,784
Mr. President,
we must not allow a mine shaft gap!

1315
01:32:47,867 --> 01:32:51,871
Sir, I have a plan.

1316
01:32:53,957 --> 01:32:56,167
<i>Mein Führer,</i>

1317
01:32:56,251 --> 01:32:58,003
I can walk!
